# ONL320 Sync Error: Unable to Set Preferred Exporter for Workspace

If you see the error:

**“ONL320 Sync Error: We're unable to set [X user] as the preferred exporter for the workspace.”**

this means there is an issue preventing the preferred exporter from being updated within the QuickBooks Online connection settings.

Until the configuration issue is reviewed and resolved, the preferred exporter cannot be changed.

---

## Why ONL320 Happens

ONL320 occurs when there is a configuration issue affecting the QuickBooks Online connection settings.

This may be related to:

- Permission restrictions  
- A connection state issue  
- Backend configuration inconsistencies  

Because the preferred exporter is tied to the QuickBooks Online integration configuration, certain issues cannot be resolved directly within Workspace settings.

This is not typically caused by general Workspace export settings.

---

## Who Can Fix ONL320

A Workspace Admin can initiate troubleshooting, but this error requires internal review.

---

## How to Fix ONL320

Please reach out to **Concierge** so the team can review the QuickBooks Online connection settings and resolve the issue.

When contacting Concierge, include:

- The Workspace name  
- The email address of the user you are trying to set as the preferred exporter  
- A screenshot of the error message  

Providing this information helps speed up troubleshooting.

---

# FAQ

## Can I fix ONL320 by reconnecting QuickBooks Online?

Not typically. This error usually requires configuration review rather than simple reconnection.

---

## Does ONL320 affect report exports?

It may prevent changes to the preferred exporter, but existing export functionality may continue to work depending on current settings.

---

## Is ONL320 caused by QuickBooks subscription limitations?

No. ONL320 is generally related to configuration or permission issues within the integration settings, not subscription tier limitations.
